"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by Freshwater UK on behalf of The Port of Tilbury&#xa0;Summary&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Port of Tilbury overview&#xa0;The tidal Thames: balancing the three pillars of sustainability&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe \nhabitats \nfor these species on the Thames are all designated as being in favourable condition; \nand \nall of the habitats and \nspecies are found elsewhere in the UK.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThis is entirely inconsistent with Government policy seeking to bear down on the burden of regulation and encourage economic growth.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nConclusion&#xa0;\n24 January 2014\n3&#xa0;\n"